text:
Desimartini Live cricket score: India A vs Australia warm-up match, Day 3: 
Catch live cricket score of India A vs Australia Day 3 of their three-day warm-up match here. Shreyas Iyer scored a brilliant half-century as India A ended Day 2 on 176/4. Earlier, Australia finished their innings on 469/7 thanks to fifties from Matthew Wade and Mitchell Marsh. Follow live score and updates here. cricket Updated: Feb 19, 2017 08:54 IST HT Correspondent Hindustan Times Shreyas Iyer’s magnificent fifty helped India A fightback in their warm-up game against Australia at the Brabourne stadium. Catch live cricket score of India A vs Australia, day 3, here.(PTI) 
India A were batting on 176/4 at the end of Day 2 against Australia cricket team in the three-day warm-up match at the Brabourne Stadium in Mumbai. Catch live cricket score of India A vs Australia Day 3 here. 
Nathan Lyon took two wickets and Jackson Bird both took two wickets, but Shreyas Iyer scored a brilliant fifty to lead the fightback for India A. 
Earlier in the day, Matthew Wade and Mitchell Marsh scored quick-fire fifties as Australia declared their first innings on 469/7. tags
